Watson, 2004). It is possible that environmental and
genetic signals could be concomitantly implicated in the
etiopathogeny, but the cellular mechanisms underlying
the death of dopaminergic neurons in PD are still not well
understood. Nonetheless, increasing evidence suggests
that programmed cell death plays a key role in the neuro-
degeneration observed in PD (Mattson, 2000). Analogous
elevations in apoptosis markers have been described in
pancreatic
b-cells
during
